data.enText: to slide sideways or forwards in an uncontrolled way

data.chText: 汽车在冰上打滑，径直撞到了墙上。
data.enText: The car skidded on the ice and went straight into the wall.

data.chText: 出租车滑行了一段路后，及时停了下来。
data.enText: The taxi skidded to a halt just in time.

data.chText: 她的脚在湿地板上一滑，重重地摔了一跤。
data.enText: Her foot skidded on the wet floor and she fell heavily.

data.chText: 侧滑；打滑；突然向一侧滑行
data.enText: the movement of a vehicle when it suddenly slides sideways in an uncontrolled way

data.chText: 摩托车朝一侧滑了出去。
data.enText: The motorbike went into a skid .

data.chText: 公路上留下的滑行痕迹说明这辆车当时开得有多快。
data.enText: The skid marks on the road showed how fast the car had been travelling.
a part that is underneath some aircraft, beside the wheels, and is used for landing
to stop sb/sth from being successful or making progress
to be in a bad situation that will get worse

tr: a restraint provided when the brake linings are moved hydraulically against the brake drum to retard the wheel's rotation
one of a pair of planks used to make a track for rolling or sliding objects
move obliquely or sideways, usually in an uncontrolled manner
example: the wheels skidded against the sidewalk
the car skidded in the curve on the wet road

tr: apply a brake or skid to

value.def: If a vehicle skids, it slides sideways or forwards while moving, for example when you are trying to stop it suddenly on a wet road.

example.ex: The car pulled up too fast and skidded on the dusty shoulder of the road...
example.tran: 由于刹车太急，车子侧滑到了满是尘土的路肩上。

example.ex: The plane skidded off the runway while taking off in a snow storm.
example.tran: 飞机在暴风雪中起飞的时候滑出了跑道。

example.ex: I slammed the brakes on and went into a skid.
example.tran: 我猛地一踩刹车，结果车子打滑了。

value.def: If you say that something is on the skids, you believe that it is out of control and certain to fail.

example.ex: His career is on the skids.

value.tran: 无法挽救的;注定要失败的

trans: (自行车、滑板运动等中戴的)防撞头盔，安全帽
(城市中流浪、失业、酗酒的人聚居的)贫民区，穷街陋巷
